s\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"Review the changes in the `feat/device-auth-login` branch compared to `main`. The diff adds ~1156 lines across 11 files implementing an OAuth device authorization flow for the `entire login` CLI command.\\n\\nHere's a summary of what was added:\\n\\n## New files:\\n1. **`cmd/entire/cli/api/base_url.go`** + test ‚Äî Resolves the Entire API base URL (defaults to `https://entire.io`, overridden by `ENTIRE_API_BASE_URL` env var)\\n2. **`cmd/entire/cli/auth/client.go`** + test ‚Äî HTTP client for device auth (POST `/oauth/device/code` to start, POST `/oauth/token` to poll)\\n3. **`cmd/entire/cli/auth/store.go`** + test ‚Äî Token persistence to `~/.config/entire/auth.json` keyed by base URL, with atomic writes (temp file + rename) and 0600 permissions\\n4. **`cmd/entire/cli/login.go`** ‚Äî The `entire login` command implementation: starts device auth, opens browser (or prints URL), polls until approval/denial/expiry, saves token\\n5. **`cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/login_test.go`** ‚Äî Integration tests using httptest server: happy path, expired flow, denied flow\\n6. **`scripts/local-device-auth-smoke.sh`** ‚Äî Manual smoke test script for local dev\\n7. **`README.md`** ‚Äî Updated with login command and local dev testing docs\\n\\n## Modified files:\\n8. **`cmd/entire/cli/root.go`** ‚Äî Registers the new `login` subcommand\\n\\nPlease review for:\\n- Security issues (token handling, URL validation, file permissions, injection risks)\\n- Correctness of the OAuth device auth flow per RFC 8628\\n- Error handling completeness\\n- Code quality, naming, idiomatic Go\\n- Test coverage gaps\\n- Any race conditions or edge cases\\n- Whether the `client_id` should be hardcoded as `\\\"entire-cli\\\"`\\n- The `openBrowser` function and any risks with exec.CommandContext\\n- Whether `browserOpener` as a package-level var is appropriate (testability vs global state)\\n- The smoke test script quality\\n\\nRead all the new files to do a thorough revie