owing CLI users to authenticate via their browser.\\n\\n### How it works\\n\\n1. CLI requests a device code from `/oauth/device/code`\\n2. User approves in their browser (opened automatically, or URL printed with `--print-browser-url`)\\n3. CLI polls `/oauth/token` until approved, denied, or expired\\n4. Token is saved to the OS keyring (macOS Keychain / Linux Secret Service / Windows Credential Manager) via `zalando/go-keyring`, matching the pattern used in the `entire` backend CLI\\n\\n### What's included\\n\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/api/`** ‚Äî Base URL resolution with `ENTIRE_API_BASE_URL` env var override, scheme validation (http/https only)\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/auth/client.go`** ‚Äî HTTP client for device auth endpoints with shared `postForm` helper, response size limits, strict/lenient JSON decoding\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/auth/store.go`** ‚Äî Keyring-backed token store (`SaveToken`, `GetToken`, `DeleteToken`, `LookupCurrentToken`)\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/login.go`** ‚Äî Login command with transient error retry (up to 5 consecutive failures), `slow_down` backoff per RFC, browser opening with fallback\\n- **`scripts/local-device-auth-smoke.sh`** ‚Äî Manual smoke test for local dev\\n\\n### Testing\\n\\n- **13 unit tests** for `waitForApproval` poll loop (success, pending, denied, expired, slow_down, empty token, transient retry/exhaustion/reset, context cancellation, expiry clamping)\\n- **8 unit tests** for keyring store (save/get, not-found, multi-URL, empty token rejection, delete, delete-noop, lookup)\\n- **2 unit tests** for JSON decoding (strict vs lenient)\\n- **3 unit tests** for base URL resolution (default, override, scheme rejection)\\n- **3 integration tests** for end-to-end login flow (happy path with approval, expired, denied) using httptest servers\\n\\n### Design decisions\\n\\n- All dependencies are injected (`deviceAuthClient` interface, `browserOpenFunc` parameter) for testability ‚Äî no package-level mutable state\\n- Token keyed by base URL in ke